 THE Federal Ministry of Works on Tuesday announced that the Apongbon Road, which had been closed for some time for repair works, will be opened today. A statement by the Federal Controller of Works Fred Adedamola Kuti disclosed that the road would be opened this morning. The statement reads: “For your information, we are opening Apongbon road tomorrow morning having completed the repair works.” Kuti commended members of the public, especially motorists for their support and patience throughout the period of the reconstruction, adding that the repaired road will now ease traffic flow in that axis of the state.